main event: Multiple witnesses observed unidentified flying objects in the sky over San Antonio, Texas, on February 26 and 27, 1953.
interesting points: Witnesses described bright lights moving rapidly with no sound,The objects appeared to be circular and brighter than the stars,Observations were made by military personnel at Brooks Air Force Base,Some witnesses reported the objects making oscillating movements and dives,No physical evidence was found to support the sightings.
witness description: Military personnel and other individuals working in the area.
